13/03/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A court in Belgrade on Monday (March 12th) sentenced 12 people, including three Chinese nationals, to a total of 45 years in prison for running a human trafficking ring. The defendants were found guilty of smuggling an unspecified number of Chinese nationals to Italy via several Balkan countries. 
In other news, customs officials in Bulgaria and Croatia seized large quantities of heroin at the weekend. Officers at Kalotina, on the border with Serbia, found more than 150kg of the drug in a Turkish truck travelling to Austria. In Croatia, customs officers at the Bajakovo checkpoint discovered about 30kg of heroin in an Italian-registered car owned by a Macedonian national. Officials say the drugs were bound for an unspecified West European country. (UPI - 12/03/07) 
